Sample_extract_protocol_ch1	"Tissue was incubated in lysis buffer (100 mM Tris HCL pH 8.5, 5 mM EDTA, 0.2% SDS, 200 mM NaCl, 100 ug/mL Proteinase K) overnight at 55C.  and disassembled using a pestle. Disassociated tissue was treated with 4 uL of Rnase A for 30 minutes at RT and then treated with ethanol overnight at -20C. 1 ug of extracted DNA per sample was treated with bisulfite and used in the assay." Sample_data_processing	"Data was analyzed in R (version 3.4.2) using minfi (1.23.4) and SVA (3.26.0). Poorly performing probes (detection p-value < 0.05) and sex chromosome probes were removed from the analysis. NOOB and functional normalization were performed using the minfi package according author guidelines. Confounding variables were detected using SVA and, alongside batch/plate effects, were accounted for using the ComBat algorithm." Confounding variables were detected using SVA and, alongside batch/plate effects, were accounted for using the ComBat algorithm." Confounding variables were detected using SVA and, alongside batch/plate effects, were accounted for using the ComBat algorithm." Confounding variables were detected using SVA and, alongside batch/plate effects, were accounted for using the ComBat algorithm." Confounding variables were detected using SVA and, alongside batch/plate effects, were accounted for using the ComBat algorithm." Confounding variables were detected using SVA and, alongside batch/plate effects, were accounted for using the ComBat algorithm."
